L4NaYcWRW1E.keywords: Ice Hockey Sport Sweden Country United States Of America Country Team USA USA Hockey Noora Raty Europe Olympics Sochi Lake PlacidWomen's Ice Hockey USA vs SwedenThe Canadian and American women's ice hockey teams dominate, only losing only to each other. The US won the first Olympic gold in 1998, Canada has won every four years since then. Will the trend contine in Sochi, or will some other nation step up to challenge for the gold? The Four Nations Cup at Lake Placid gives a preview of the 2014 games. A hot goalie is a game changer, and it was Finland's Noora Raty who stopped almost a shot a minute to lead her team to an upset victory over eigning world champion Team USA. After losing their two pool games, Team USA was pumped and dangerous as they took the ice against Sweden in the consolation round. The Americans pressured the goal throughout the early play. Midway through the first period they broke through when Ksatie Bresser found a corner of the net for her first goal in international competition. Eight minutes later Brianna Decker poked home a rebound for a 20 USA lead. Sweden scored in the closing moments of the period to keep the game close, but the Americans had taken charge, posting a 14 to 2 edge in shotsongoal edge. In the second period the American's relentless pressure paid off. At 404 Kelli Stack found the back net. The Swedes became frustrated. They were taking penalties. The US had a two skater advantage when Jocelyn Lameroux slipped a shot into the cords. Within 99 seconds Team USA scored twice more to take a commanding 61 lead.

HkH9ld2L4a8.keywords: Magic the Gathering mtg duels of plainswalkers plains walkers dotp dotpw xbla xbox xbox massive damageMagic The Gathering DotPW XBLA  7395 DamageSorry about the shitty capture. I had no intention of doing this, it just sort of happened. I tried to get my DVD recorder ready in time but it was giving me troubles so I just grabbed the camcorder. Anyway, this is a massive amount of damage being dealt in Magic The Gathering Duels of the Plainswalkers for XBox Live Arcade. You followin me camera guy? I was using the elf deck and I got really fucking lucky and drew both a Imperious Perfect and Immaculate Magistrate first turn, and managed to destroy all of the enemies creatures in time to get them out. At this point, we're almost at the bottom of our decks, but what you see in the first half of the video is what I've been doing the entire game adding a 11 elf creature and giving 11 for each elf to another creature each turn. The 11's actually came out as a lot higher than that because I had several creatures already in play to pump them up. My last draw was fucking insane. By the end I had more than 70 creatures in play, all elves, and all of them except for about 30 token creatures were already ranging from 3030's to 105105's. The Coat of Arms gives all your creatures 11 for each creature they share a type with, so that was an instant 7070 or more to each and every one of them. I totally forgot that card was even in the deck! I'm glad I drew it before my opponent ran out of cards. As if you can't tell, the AI was bugging out the whole game. I heard that it just runs a bunch of possible scenarios in the background and uses the best one to decide which cards to play, but considering how long the thinking times were despite the fact that he didn't play a single card other than a land for about 40 turns, I'm guessing it realized it had no way out and was trying to give up. Stupid ragequitting AI. Anyway, I noticed he had thrown out all his Holy Days on discards, so I held off until he had 2 cards left in his deck before I attacked. I was gonna do it at five because I couldn't remember if there were 3 or 4 Holy Days in that deck, but there were 3 in his graveyard so even if he was hiding one I still would have gotten another shot at it next turn. Good thing I held off though, otherwise I wouldn't have landed the Coat of Arms and probably only would have ended up with about 10002000 damage.
